# TEAM STUFF



Matt

Does the average energy used per day change from 2007 to 2009?

\(\bf{H_0:}\) There is no difference in the average energy used per day in 2007 and in 2009.

\(\bf{H_1:}\) There is a significant difference in average energy used per day in 2007 and in 2009.

Test Statistic: average difference in energy used per day

This is important because if there is a change in energy consumption from 2007 to 2009, we would probably see a change in the average energy used per day. Similarly, if there is not a change in energy consumption from 2007 to 2009, we will probably not see a change in the average energy used per day.


mattdf <- energy %>%
  group_by(Date) %>% summarize(average= mean(Global_active_power)) %>%
  mutate(Year=as.factor(format(Date, '%Y')), DayOfYear=as.numeric(format(Date,'%j'))) %>% select(DayOfYear, Year, average)
matt2007 <- mattdf %>% filter(Year==2007)
matt2009 <- mattdf %>% filter(Year==2009)
Iterate <- function(A, B, n) {
  set.seed(1)
  C <-  vector("double", nrow(A))
  for (i in c(1:n)) { # Do n times
    x <- rbinom(size=1,n=nrow(A), prob=0.5)
    for (j in c(1:nrow(A))){ # For each day of the year
      if(x[[j]]==1){
        C[[j]] = C[[j]] + as.numeric(A[j,3]) - as.numeric(B[j,3])
      }else {
        C[[j]] = C[[j]] + as.numeric(B[j,3]) - as.numeric(B[j,3])
      }
    }
  }
  for(i in c(1:length(C))){
    C[[i]] = C[[i]]/n
  }
  return(C)
}
random <- Iterate(matt2007, matt2009, 1000)
real <- matt2009[,3] - matt2007[,3]

toPlot <- tibble(
  DayOfYear = matt2007$DayOfYear,
  random = random,
  real = real$average,
  difference = real-random
  
)
ggplot(data=toPlot, aes(x=DayOfYear)) + 
  geom_smooth(aes(y=real),se=F, color="green3") + 
  geom_smooth(aes( y=random), se=F, color="orange2") +
  labs(x="Day of the Year", y="Difference between group A and group B")

The green line is the difference between average daily energy usage in 2007 and 2009.

The orange line is the difference between average daily energy useage in two groups. The groups were made by randomly swapping the daily average for days in the 2007 and 2009 datasets.

Conclusion
These lines are very different, so we reject \(H_0\) in favor of \(H_1\) We conclude that there is a difference between the average daily energy useage in 2009 and 2007.

New Tools:
- Use of functions
- Use of for loops
- Use of Hypothesis tests
